summary: The thing about Harry is, though, that he doesn't just say "treat people with kindness". He does it, he lives it, he IS it. It's...
body: The thing about Harry is, though, that he doesn’t just say “treat people with kindness”. He does it, he lives it, he IS it. It’s not just a catchphrase. It’s his ideology. He’s not just saying it for it to promote him, but he says and does everything to promote it. He makes a safe space for all people wherever he goes. He promotes statements that talk about equality. He waves (not only pride but also Black Lives Matter) flags and gently talks to fans who come out to him, while being considerate of their feelings and privacy. He pays attention to everyone that works with him, even the “smaller” people, and treats them as equals, even if he’s a star and they’re “just little people”, he doesn’t make them feel like little people. I could go on and on for days about his sweetness, his kindness, his realness when it comes to that saying that has become associated with him. I could not be prouder to have such a wonderful idol 💖
